__cs__ And she was unusual because she was really interested in a new science , the emerging field of epidemiology , the study of patterns in disease .
__cs__ But like every scientist , she appreciated that to make her mark , what she needed to do was find a hard problem and solve it .
__cs__ The hard problem that Alice chose was the rising incidence of childhood cancers .
__cs__ Most disease is correlated with poverty , but in the case of childhood cancers , the children who were dying seemed mostly to come from affluent families .
__cs__ So , what , she wanted to know , could explain this anomaly ?
__cs__ Now , Alice had trouble getting funding for her research .
